Real Madrid have announced their squad that will face Club Brugge in today’s UEFA Champions League clash at the Santiago Bernabeu. Real Madrid coach, Zinedine Zidane, released a list to 19 players to tackle the visitors on the club’s official Twitter page. The La Liga giants head to the game following a goalless draw with Atletico Madrid in the La Liga over the weekend. Below is Real Madrid’s squad against Club Brugge: Goalkeepers: Courtois, Areola, Altube, Defenders: Carvajal, Militao, Ramos, Varane, Nacho, Marcelo Midfielders: Kroos, Modric, Casemiro, Valverde,Isco Forwards: Hazard, Benzema, Lucas, Jovic, Vinicius The kick-off time for the match is 5:55pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.